\subsection{Identity component of a Sato-Tate group}
\begin{definition}\label{st_group.identity_component}
\uses{st_group.component_group,st_group.definition}
The **identity component** of a {{KNOWL('st_group.definition', 'Sato-Tate group')}} $G$ is the connected component $G^0$ of the identity element.  As a compact Lie group, the identity component $G^0$ is a normal subgroup of finite index.  The quotient $G/G^0$ is the {{KNOWL('st_group.component_group', "component group")}} of $G$.
\end{definition}


